# Downloaded Toolathlon-Trajectories JSONL (large, CC-BY-4.0 — not ours to vendor; re-fetch on demand)
_data/

# mermaid-cli install for rendering the EXPLAINER diagrams — regenerable, never vendor it
node_modules/
package.json
package-lock.json
# ...but DO keep the rendered diagram sources + high-res PNGs (durable deliverables):
!_diagrams/

# Replay output: ignore everything by default (regenerable)...
_results/*
# ...EXCEPT the durable, small, self-contained deliverables — kept in-repo so the study survives
# across agents (the operator's "data in a durable format to explore" requirement):
!_results/replay_all_rows.csv      # the flat per-run rows — the explorable unit
!_results/replay_all.json          # the aggregate + per-model grids (what viz.py reads)
!_results/schema.md                # the rows' column documentation
!_results/fig1_purchase_vs_capability.png
!_results/fig2_per_model_grid.png
!_results/fig3_simpson.png
!_results/fig4_confusion.png
!_results/fig5_lift_vs_recall.png
!_results/fig6_trio_additivity.png
# docs/158 terminal_error additivity: the durable claims ledger + the 3 reproducible figures.
# NB: git negation lines must NOT carry trailing inline comments (the `#` becomes part of the
# pattern and silently breaks the match) — keep the path bare, comment on its own line above.
!_results/additivity_claims.md
!_results/figA_additivity_headline.png
!_results/figB_per_model_catches.png
!_results/figC_frontier_sensitivity.png
!_results/figD_combined_dos_lift.png
# docs/160 SOTA positioning: the trained-classifier head-to-head ledger (durable, reproducible).
!_results/classifier_comparison.md
!_results/.gitkeep

# docs/161 LIVE Gemini run: ignore the large downloaded run dirs (trajectories, workspaces,
# conversation histories — regenerable from the public service)...
_live/*
# ...EXCEPT the small, durable, self-contained scored-rows CSV (one row per task) + the task lists,
# so the live study survives across agents the same way the replay rows do. Negation paths stay
# BARE — a trailing inline comment becomes part of the pattern and silently breaks the match.
!_live/results/
_live/results/*
!_live/results/live_scored_rows.csv
!_live/results/local_scored_rows.csv
!_live/results/ab_pilot_run1.md
!_live/results/ab_flash_run.md
!_live/results/ab_scored_rows.csv
!_live/run_local_batch.sh
!_live/tasklists/
